Pipeline Analytics Template

Use Pipeline Analytics to plug your pipeline snapshot data into a ready-made waterfall dashboard. You get instant insight into how the pipeline changes between two snapshots.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To create and manage the Pipeline Analytics app: Manage CRM Analytics Templated Apps
To use the Pipeline Analytics app: Use CRM Analytics Templated Apps

The template’s configuration wizard takes you through a step-by-step process to make it easy to get a cool waterfall chart showing your pipeline. You don’t have to manually import data or create a dashboard from scratch in CRM Analytics Studio.

IMPORTANT See Create Apps from CRM Analytics Templates: Start Here for general app creation procedures for all CRM Analytics templated apps.

Org Requirements
Make sure you and all app users have the CRM Analytics license.
Make sure you and others who create the app have the ‘Use Any API Client’ permission.

A snapshotted dataset with pipeline data is required. The source of your data can be any standard or custom object, a CSV file, or an external tool.

The dataset you use in the waterfall must include fields that contain the following data or app creation fails:
Amount (measure)
Is closed (yes/no; boolean)
Is won (yes/no; boolean)
Unique ID
Close date (dimension)
Snapshot date

You answer questions in the eight-question wizard to select a dataset and fields required to create the waterfall.

Use Pipeline Analytics
Open the app.
Select CRM Analytics Studio to open the CRM Analytics home page.
Under Browse, select All Items.
Select the Apps tab, then click your app to open it.

Change filter selections in the dashboard to dig deeper into your pipeline. Available filters depend on your selections in the last question of the wizard.
